<H3> <TI>   DPRK `Ready' To Propose Compromise to U.S. </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK `Ready' To Propose Compromise to U.S. </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706024194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0220 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1706024194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 17 KYODO -- North Korea is ready to 
propose a compromise package to the United States to solve the 
standoff over its nuclear program if bilateral talks are held, a 
Japanese politician Friday [17 June] quoted a senior North 
Korean official as saying. 
  Kim Yong-sun, (North) Korean Workers' Party Secretary in 
charge of International Affairs, made the remarks in a meeting 
late Thursday with Taku Yamasaki, former director general of the 
Defense Agency and a Liberal Democratic Party (LDP) Diet member, 
Yamasaki told reporters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

