the observation tower overlooking the scenery of the gigantic 
West Sea Barrage cutting across the rough sea in an eight 
kilometre section. 
  Carter commanded a bird's-eye view of the West Sea Barrage, 
hearing an explanation about the barrage, one of the great 
creations of the Workers' Party era. 

