  [Text] A Myanmar [Burmese] delegation led by U Ohn Gyaw, 
minister of foreign affairs and chairman of the National 
Commission for Environmental Affairs, this afternoon left Yangon 
[Rangoon] by air to attend the ministerial level environmental 
conference of the Asia and Pacific Region, Eco Asia '94, to be 
held in (Saitama) in Japan from 21 to 23 June, at the 
invitation of Miss Toshiko Hamayotsu, director general of the 
Environmental Agency, minister responsible for the world 
environmental problems, and minister of the Government Office. 
  The Myanmar delegation was seen off at the Yangon airport by 
ministers, responsible personnel, and family members. 
  The members of the Myanmar delegation also includes U Thein 
Han, Myanmar ambassador to Japan, and Charge d'Affaires U Kyaw 
Tint Shwe. 

