<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Singapore </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister: Need To Remain Active in Economy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister: Need To Remain Active in Economy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1706154994 Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation in 
English 1100 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1706154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Singapore Singapore Broadcasting Corporation </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Trade and Industry Minister Yeo Cheow Tong has 
proposed a two-step approach to keep Singapore active in the 
global economy. He said the government will continue to come out 
with competitive strategy to further strengthen the domestic 
economy which will be the mainstay of the nation's prosperity. 
In addition, Singapore must create more economic space by 
becoming a partner of growth in the Asia-Pacific region. 
  Mr. Yeo was speaking at the Singapore International Chamber 
of Commerce luncheon. He said given the abundant regional 
opportunities, Singapore's external economy should grow rapidly 
to match that of Switzerland and the Netherlands. At present, 
our level of private investment abroad is only about two-thirds 
of these two countries. However, Mr. Yeo stressed that 
Singapore must ensure a right balance between the domestic and 
external pressures. The growth of the external economy should 
complement and not fall out with the domestic one. 

</TEXT>

