<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Philippine National Police [PNP] Chief Ricaredo 
Sarmiento has confirmed the presence of Abu Sayyaf members in 
Metro Manila. He said the PNP suspects the terrorists are 
recruiting new members from Muslim communities in the 
metropolis. Sarmiento said security measures have been taken by 
the police, who fear that besides their recruitment mission the 
Abu Sayyaf men may carry out sabotage and other terroristic acts 
as they have been doing in Mindanao. PNP intelligence agents 
have reported sighting the extremists in the Muslim center in 
Quiapo and other Muslim communities in Taguig and Tandang Sora 
in Quezon City. 

