<H3> <TI>   SDPJ: Party's To Propose Broad Coalition </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SDPJ: Party's To Propose Broad Coalition </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1706144094 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 17 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1706144094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Speaking at a lecture in Tokyo on the afternoon of 
16 June, Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] General 
Secretary Wataru Kubo touched on a coalition blueprint the SDPJ 
plans to submit as early as next week. He said: "Even if we 
place our policies highly, this does not always meet the 
people's expectations. Our policies should be broad ones that 
can win the support of the various coalition parties." In this 
way, he indicated his view that in hammering out the party's 
alliance proposal, the party will give priority to basic 
agreements reached with the ruling parties. 

</TEXT>

