<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Surin: France Unwilling To Give Arms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Surin: France Unwilling To Give Arms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1906131994 Bangkok THE SUNDAY NATION in English 19 Jun 94 
p A2 </F>

<F P=103> BK1906131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok THE SUNDAY NATION </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] France is not ready to grant a Cambodian government 
request for arms to fight the Khmer Rouge. Deputy Foreign 
Minister Surin Phitsuwan said yesterday after a recent meeting 
with the French foreign affairs permanent secretary. 
  Surin added that Australia, which had also been approached 
by 
the Cambodian government, had made no decision on the matter and 
the United States was only interested in supporting military 
training in Cambodia. 
  Surin, who returned from an overseas tour, stopped over in 
France after he attended a meeting of ambassadors and 
counsellors in Morocco. He arrived in Bangkok from Kuala Lumpur 
yesterday. 
  Apart from narcotics suppression and the Cambodian conflict, 
Surin said the talks with French officials included discussion 
on SEA 10, a Southeast Asian grouping which includes the six in 
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), the three 
Indochinese nations and Burma. 

</TEXT>

