<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Labor Minister Discusses Ties With Official </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Labor Minister Discusses Ties With Official </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2006101394 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2006101394 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuwait has shown keen interests in employing more 
Thai workers to help in reconstruction of the country. Vice 
President of the Kuwaiti Parliament [Salei Yusuf Al Fathala] met 
Minister of Labor and Social Welfare Phaithun Kaeothong on 
Friday for talks on Thai labor in Kuwait. There are currently 
about 3,000 Thai workers in Kuwait. The country wishes to 
increase the number of Thai workers to 7,000, the same number 
employed in Kuwait before the Gulf war. The vice president of 
the Kuwaiti parliament asked Thailand to help urge Iraq to 
release Kuwaiti prisoners of war. Kuwait intends to cooperate 
more in Thailand in diplomatic, trade, and labor areas. Trade 
between the two countries last year amounted to 2,000 million 
baht. Kuwait has invested over 1,000 million baht in the 
petroleum business in Thailand. Kuwait has also invited 
Minister Phaithun to visit that country. 

</TEXT>

