<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Phalang Tham Party's Spokeswoman Resigns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1706135694 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1706135694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A deputy spokesperson attached to the Prime 
Minister's Office this morning announced her resignation from 
the post together with the assistant secretary to the prime 
minister and a member of the group of whips for parties in the 
coalition government. All three persons are Phalang Tham Party 
MP's who endorsed the submission of a motion calling for the 
establishment of a special commission to redraft the 
Constitution. 
  Mrs. Sudarat Keyuraphan, deputy spokesperson for the Prime 
Minister's Office, said that she decided to resign from the post 
because she wanted to fully perform her duty as a Member of 
Parliament mainly for the sake of the people and country. 

