<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate Accepts House-Approved Copyright Bill </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senate Accepts House-Approved Copyright Bill </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1706132094 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in Thai 0530 GMT 
17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1706132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  Thai </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Senate meeting convened at Parliament this 
morning at 0935. The meeting considered the house-approved 
draft copyright bill. A number of senators debated in support 
of the bill saying that it will contribute to developing the 
national economy to be in line with the world economic 
situation. They said this will lead to greater development of 
the country's economy because it will also result in expansion 
of trade and industry. The draft bill will encourage Thai 
people to be enthusiastic in using new and modern inventions. 
  Deputy Commerce Minister Churin Laksanawisit said that the 
draft copyright bill will provide protection for data work and 
actors' achievements. Regarding computer programs, over which 
many parties have expressed concerns, they will be protected by 
the existing law. 
  After a considerable period of debate, the meeting decided 
to 
accept in principle the draft bill before being passed for 
further consideration by the commission. The meeting was 
adjourned at 1210. 
  Earlier, it took the House of Representatives three weeks to 
deliberate and approve this draft copyright bill. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

