<H3> <TI>   Vice Minister Meets Japanese Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vice Minister Meets Japanese Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1806074794 Hanoi VNA in English 1519 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1806074794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 17 -- Japan's unchangeable policy is 
to develop its cooperation with Vietnam despite political 
changes in Tokyo, said Japanese Foreign Minister Kakizawa while 
receiving yesterday Vice Foreign Minister Vu Khoan who was 
attending an international meeting there. 
  Both Mr Kakizawa and Mr Vu Khoan expressed their pleasure at 
the expansion and consolidation of the friendly and cooperative 
reactions between the countries, especially those following 
Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet's visit to Japan. They also 
exchanged views on measures to be taken to further those 
relations. 
  On the same day, Mr Vu Khoan had a meeting with Mr. A. 
Nishigaki, chairman of the Overseas Economic Cooperation Fund 
(OECF) during which host and guest exchanged views on the 
implementation of Japan's aid programme for Vietnam and things 
to be done for their effective cooperation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

