<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   IMF Grants Vietnam $50-Million Loan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IMF Grants Vietnam $50-Million Loan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1906125094 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 17 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1906125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The International Monetary Fund has announced to 
grant Vietnam a loan of $50 million for the rehabilitation of 
economic development in Vietnam in 1994. 
  Meanwhile the World Bank lent Vietnam credit for the 
upgrading of the section from Ho Chi Minh city to Can Tho and 
the section between Hanoi and Nhatrang on Highway No.1. The 
World Bank also provided loans for the improvement of primary 
education system and agricultural development program, including 
three such projects for agricultural credit, rubber plantation, 
and intensive farming. 
  The World Bank expert said that in the coming three or four 
years, international credits to vietnam will reach $315 million 
per year. 

</TEXT>

