<H3> <TI>   Further on National Assembly Proceedings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on National Assembly Proceedings </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    17 Jun Proceedings </H4>

<F P=102> BK1706143294 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1706143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, National Assembly deputies continued work in 
the Ba Dinh Conference Hall to debate and pass chapters six to 
17 of the draft labor code under the direction of National 
Assembly Vice Chairman Phung Van Tuu. 
  The majority of deputies agreed to pass chapter six on 
wages, 
chapter seven on working hours and break times, chapter eight on 
work discipline and material responsibility, chapter nine on 
working safety and sanitation, chapter 10 on separate 
stipulations for female workers, chapter 11 on separate 
stipulations for juvenile and other workers, chapter 12 on 
social insurance, chapter 13 on worker unions, chapter 14 on 
labor disputes, chapter 15 on state management over labor, 
chapter 16 on state inspection of labor and punishment for labor 
law violations, and chapter 17 on the implementation clause. 
  The drafting committee for the draft labor code presented 
the 
draft after receiving opinions from National Assembly deputies. 
At the conclusion of this afternoon's session, the National 
Assembly agreed to pass the entire draft labor code and 
empowered the National Assembly Standing Committee to reexamine 
all details a final time before presenting it to the state 
president for promulgation. 
  Tomorrow, the National Assembly will continue its work in 
the 
conference hall. 

</TEXT>

