<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Securities Market Decrees Under Close Study </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Securities Market Decrees Under Close Study </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2006155494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2006155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The State Bank reported recently that the 
Government Loans Market Research Committee has completed three 
draft legal documents related to establishing a securities 
market in Vietnam. 
  The draft document on setting up the securities market 
specified tasks to be carried out from now until the 
establishment of a liaison office for the market. 
  The draft decree on stocks and securities market is composed 
of 101 articles dealing with the issuance, posting, selling, and 
transferring of stocks and shares; foreign investment in 
securities; and capital and bonds of companies and corporations. 
  The draft decree for a National Securities Committee 
stipulates that the committee is an independent administrative 
agency affiliated with the government. 
  These three draft documents have been submitted to the 
Monetary and Financial Council and have been highly appraised by 
the government. 

</TEXT>

