<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Long An Provides More Household Electricity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Long An Provides More Household Electricity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1906155194 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1906155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Long An has invested tens of billion of dong to 
build a medium-voltage power line linked with the national 
electric network. The local people have contributed 50 percent 
of the construction cost. 
  At present, 130 of the 180 villages and wards of the 
province 
use electricity supplied by the national grid. All 32 villages 
of Duc Hoa and Chau Thanh districts have been provided with 
electricity for home use and production. 
  Long An is striving to supply electricity to all villages in 
the province in 1995 using its own budget, money collected from 
electric fees, and funds contributed by the local people. 

</TEXT>

