<H3> <TI>   Fijian President Arrives for Five-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fijian President Arrives for Five-Day Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1906084394 Hong Kong AFP in English 0909 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1906084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Noumea, June 18 (AFP) -- Fijian President Ratu Sir 
Kamisese Mara arrived Saturday in New Caledonia for a five-day 
official visit at the invitation of the French Government. 
  The Fijian leader, who received military honors after 
arriving from the French territory of Wallis and Futuna, called 
for closer relations with New Caledonia. 
  He stressed that his country had no objections to French 
policy in the South Pacific, particularly since the start of the 
moratorium on nuclear testing in French Polynesia. 
  The president was to meet Saturday with members of the 
Fijian 
community in New Caledonia. 
  On Monday he will visit the headquarters of the Commission 
of 
the South Pacific and the Agency for the Development of Kanak 
Culture, before meeting with representatives of New Caledonian 
political parties and institutions. 
  He is scheduled to leave the territory on Wednesday. 

</TEXT>

