<H3> <TI>   Reportage on North-South Summit Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on North-South Summit Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Thorough' Preparations Ordered </H4>

<F P=102> SK2006004094 Seoul YONHAP in English 0036 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2006004094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 20 (YONHAP) -- President Kim Yong-sam 
ordered thorough preparations for a possible inter-Korean summit 
Monday, calling it an event "that may change our post-liberation 
history." 
  Kim made the instructions after a unification-related 
ministerial meeting was held earlier in the day chaired by 
Deputy Premier Yi Yong-tok. 
  The chances of an inter-Korean summit -- the first ever -- 
are at an all-time high with the top leaders of both South and 
North Korea agreeing in principle to the meeting. 
  Deputy Premier Yi pointed out that the government held a 
series of meetings over the weekend to lay out specifics for the 
South-North summit. 
  "The meeting participants are very much in tune with each 
other, allowing for rapid progress," said Yi. 

</TEXT>

