<H3> <TI>   Reportage on North-South Summit Proposal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on North-South Summit Proposal </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Share Prices Jump in Anticipation </H4>

<F P=102> SK2006084794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0840 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2006084794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 20 (YONHAP) -- Share prices jumped 
sharply at the Korean Stock Exchange on Monday at the report of 
a possible South-North summit meeting. 
  The leading composite stock price index was up 16.31 points, 
or 1.76 percent, over the weekend to finish at 942.50. 
  Besides the summit issue, the stock authorities' decision to 
allow three Hyundai firms' issues to be transacted off-board 
contributed to the overall surge. 
  Volume was large with 49 million shares changing hands at 
900 
billion won (1,116.62 million U.S. dollars). 
  Advancing issues overwhelmed decliners 632 to 181 with 76 
others remaining unchanged. Mining and insurance were only 
major issues that slid. The rise of construction, trade and 
banking issues was especially sharp. 

</TEXT>

