<H3> <TI>   Japan Asked To Aid Possible ROK `Evacuation' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan Asked To Aid Possible ROK `Evacuation' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1906101394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0900 GMT 19 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1906101394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["YONHAP report from Tokyo"] </F>
  [Text] According to Japan's YOMIURI SHIMBUN, the United 
States requested Japan to support the emergency evacuation of 
foreigners in the ROK, including U.S. citizens, when Japan 
begins to transport Japanese people in the ROK back to Japan in 
the case of an extremely tense situation on the Korean peninsula. 
  YOMIURI SHIMBUN today quoted a Japanese Government source as 
saying that, upon the request, the government is hurrying the 
revision of laws concerning the Self-Defense Force to enable the 
Self-Defense Force to dispatch its aircraft for the 
transportation of foreigners. The Japanese Government is also 
reviewing the immigration and customs process for an emergency, 
and the deployment of naval vessels for mass transportation. 
  The source said when President Clinton had a telephone 
conversation with Japanese Prime Minister Hata on 14 June, 
President Clinton conveyed his intention to build up U.S. Forces 
in the ROK and asked Japan to help transport Americans. 

</TEXT>

