<F P=103> SK1906013294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [YONHAP report from Tokyo] </F>
  [Text] Japan's SANKEI SHIMBUN reported that President Kim 
Yong-sam and Japanese Prime Minister Hata will hold summit talks 
from 2 to 3 July at Cheju Island to discuss the North Korean 
nuclear issue. 
  Quoting a ROK Government source, SANKEI SHIMBUN reported 
today that the two countries decided to hold the summit talks to 
harmonize positions on the North Korean nuclear issue before the 
G-7 meeting slated to be held beginning 8 July in Italy. 
  SANKEI SHIMBUN explained that Cheju Island has been 
designated as the meeting place because it is recognized that it 
is important to follow Western-style summit diplomacy -- holding 
frequent meetings in an informal atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

