<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports 17 Jun U.S. Air `War Exercise' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Reports 17 Jun U.S. Air `War Exercise' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1906105494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1025 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1906105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 19 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists 
Friday staged a frantic war exercise against the North by 
massively hurling nuclear-capable F-15 fighter-bombers, FA-18 
pursuit-assault planes, AV-8 VTOL [Vertical Take-Off and 
Landing] assault planes, AE-6 electronic jamming planes, KC-135 
refueling tankers based in the Pacific and fighter planes of the 
U.S. Air Force present in South Korea into the sky above Tokjok 
Islet, Pyongchang, Yongwol, Tongduchon and Kapyong of South 
Korea, according to military sources. 
  On the same day, an overseas-based RC-135 strategic 
reconnaissance plane carried out photograph shooting and 
electronic reconnaissance on the whole areas of the northern 
half of Korea in the air above Yangyang, Yangpyong and Tokjok 
Islet of South Korea. 

</TEXT>

