<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-118 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  18 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commentary Denounces Buildup of U.S. Forces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commentary Denounces Buildup of U.S. Forces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2006044594 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1225 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2006044594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1225 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Commentary by Yun Pyong-son: "Strong-Arm Measures Will Not </F>
Work"] 
  [Text] The U.S. imperialists have been bringing the 
situation on the Korean peninsula to a more and more dangerous 
phase of war under the pretext of our so-called nuclear issue. 
According to reports, on 17 June the U.S. Senate babbled about 
someone else's southward invasion and adopted a resolution 
urging President Clinton to beef up immediately the U.S. Forces 
occupying South Korea. This resolution, which passed a full 
session of the U.S. Senate, calls for, among other things, 
sending additional U.S. troops and fighter planes to South Korea 
and deploying an aircraft carrier-based combat unit in this 
region. This is an attempt to deploy massive aggression forces 
on the Korean peninsula and clearly discloses the U.S. 
imperialists' brigandish [kangdojok], aggressive nature. 
  They cited someone else's southward invasion and nuclear 
issue as a pretext for beefing up the forces. However, this is 
sophism which cannot convince anyone. 
  It is a well-known fact that the North's nuclear issue, a 
byproduct of the imperialists' antisocialist, anti-Republic 
maneuvers, is a falsehood that was fabricated to crush [apsal] 
our Republic. The same is true with threats of southward 
invasion. 
  Southward invasion, the nuclear issue, and other things that 
the U.S. imperialists are talking about are mere excuses to 
justify their military buildup and aggression maneuvers. 
  Under such excuses, the U.S. imperialists have already 
brought numerous aggression troops into South Korea and plan to 
move aircraft carriers Independence and Constellation, which had 
been mobilized in the Rimpac-94 joint military exercise, to the 
waters close to the Korean peninsula to stand by right after the 
exercise is over. They also plan to deploy aircraft carrier 
Kitty Hawk to the waters close to our country. A foreign news 
agency has disclosed that the scheduled concentration of several 
aircraft carriers in one region was part of the U.S. plan to 
beef up naval forces in Northeast Asia. Nevertheless, without 
being satisfied with this, they plan to deploy more troops and 
fighter planes and an aircraft carrier-based combat unit in 
South Korea and in its neighborhood. This proves that they plan 
to deliberately further aggravate the situation on the Korean 
peninsula to provoke a second Korea war against us at all costs. 
  If this had not been true, why should the United States have 
continuously deployed aggression forces in South Korea and in 
its neighborhood and inspected bases of the Japanese maritime 
and air Self-Defense Forces under the pretext of our so-called 
nuclear issue, which could not be used as an excuse? 
  Even though the cold war is said to be over internationally, 
the cold war has continued on the Korean peninsula because of 
the U.S. imperialists. 
  The U.S. imperialists try to launch a surprise preemptive 
strike at our Republic after deploying massive aggression forces 
under the pretext of our nuclear issue. However, military 
adventures, threats, and blackmailing can in no way frighten 
anyone else or resolve the issue. 
  The United States gave rise to the nuclear issue on the 
Korean peninsula, which originated from the U.S. imperialists' 
hostile policy toward Korea. Therefore, the nuclear issue on 
the Korean peninsula must be resolved through dialogue and 
negotiations; it can never be resolved through forcible 
pressures, threats, or blackmailing against the other side. 
  This is why people from all walks of life in the world 
denounce the U.S. imperialists for pursuing military strong-arm 
measures and strongly ask the United States to resolve the 
nuclear issue through dialogue and negotiations. 
  Just like a thief turning on the victim with a club, the 
United States, which gave rise to the nuclear issue, finds fault 
with us, who are under nuclear threat, and tries to beef up 
aggression forces. This clearly shows it has no interest in 
peacefully resolving the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula 
but tries to crush [apsal] our Republic by military force. 
  No strong-arm measures will work on us, who consider 
independence to be their life. 
  We have already made it clear that if the United States 
chooses to take strong-arm measures, we will take a different 
road. 
  If the United States tries to get something through military 
adventures, this will be a miscalculation. 
  The U.S. imperialists must clearly know we are ready for 
both 
dialogue and war and act with discretion. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-29551 </DOCNO>
