<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Criticizes French Support for Sanctions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Criticizes French Support for Sanctions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1806164094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1544 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1806164094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["A DPRK FM Spokesman Says French Authorities Should Ponder </F>
Over Matters" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 18 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the 
DPRK Foreign Ministry [FM] answered a question put by KCNA today 
regarding the fact that the French Government has recently 
danced duet with the United States in the clamor for "sanctions" 
against the DPRK, thus aggravating the situation in Korea. 
  He said: 
  Some time ago, the French Foreign Ministry claimed "a 
decisive measure against North Korea", manifesting its official 
stand to support a UN resolution on "sanctions". 
  Earlier, during U.S. President Bill Clinton visit to France, 
the French prime minister and government officials agreed to his 
proposal for "sanctions" against the DPRK. 
  Such moves of France are aimed at preventing the "nuclear 
issue" which has become an international focal point from being 
solved through DPRK-U.S. talks, having a greater say by poking 
its nose into the matter, goading Northeast Asian countries onto 
a conflict and thereby fishing in troubled waters. 
  The situation in our country now has become extremely 
strained due to the anti-DPRK moves of the United States and its 
followers. 
  Our people are making full preparations to defend the 
dignity 
and sovereignty of the country in face of the enemy's moves. 
  The French authorities cannot be ignorant of the fact that 
"sanctions" against the DPRK under such circumstances may lead 
the situation to a catastrophic phase. 
  Nevertheless, France fell in with the United States' view in 
the clamor for "sanctions" without any idea of its own and 
danced to the tune of others, edging itself into other's [words 
indistinct] for the convocation of an international conference, 
[words indistinct] to shame. Judging from this, one can see 
clearly that France is not interested at all in the question of 
defusing the present crisis on the Korean peninsula but 
persistently seeking to gratify its sinister aims. 
  We cannot but throw into question the reckless behavior of 
the French authorities. 
  We have already declared more than once that in case any 
"sanctions" should be imposed on us not only the parties taking 
the van in enforcing them but also those who back them would be 
held responsible. 
  The French authorities must know that our warning is not an 
empty word and ponder over the matter. 
  If France wants to save its face and discharge its 
responsibility as a permanent member of the UN Security Council, 
it should help toward a peaceful solution of the nuclear issue 
on the Korean peninsula through dialogue and negotiation, 
instead on joining in the act of bringing the issue into 
extremes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

