<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Activities Commemorate Kim Chong-il Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Symposiums Held on WPK Work </H4>

<F P=102> SK1806043794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0425 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1806043794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 18 (KCNA) -- Symposiums of working 
people's organizations were held to mark the lapse of 30 years 
since the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il began to work at the 
Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK]. 
  Speeches were made at the symposiums on different subjects 
such as "The dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il's idea and theory 
of building working people's organizations is immortal grand 
programme of building mass organizations of our times", "Dear 
Comrade Kim Chong-il is an illustrious leader who has most 
successfully solved the question of education of young people". 
  Speakers said that from the first days of his leadership of 
the party work Comrade Kim Chong-il attached great importance to 
the work of building working people's organizations and has 
energetically led them to discharge their mission and role as 
peripheral organizations of the party. 
  Noting that the party and the revolutionary ranks have been 
cemented rockfirm as militant ranks of loyal subjects and filial 
people and the country has turned into an indestructible 
socialist power not wavering in face of any politico-ideological 
offensive and military threats of the imperialists and 
reactionaries, they said this is entirely a result of the 
tireless, energetic activities and leadership of Comrade Kim 
Chong-il. 
  They said the most important of feats performed by Comrade 
Kim Chong-il is that he has reared young people as lifeguards, 
death-defying corps loyal to the party, thereby guaranteeing a 
bright future of the party and the revolution. The five million 
young people now are firmly prepared to be guns and bombs 
defending the party and the leader with their lives no matter 
what mad wind may blow in their way, they declared. 
  Symposiums also took place in the provinces. 

</TEXT>

