<H3> <TI>   Tokyo Positive on DPRK-ROK Summit Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tokyo Positive on DPRK-ROK Summit Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Hata Comments </H4>

<F P=102> OW1806112194 Tokyo KYODO in English 1111 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1806112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 18 KYODO -- Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata 
on Saturday welcomed the proposed summit between the North and 
South Korean leaders and expressed hope for its success. 
  "The fact that things have gone that far means a good 
climate 
has been produced. I hope the summit will succeed by all 
means," Hata told reporters. 
  He was commenting on reports from Seoul that South Korean 
President Kim Yong-sam has accepted his North Korean counterpart 
Kim Il-song's offer to hold a bilateral summit without any 
conditions to discuss the 15-month-old row over Pyongyang's 
suspected nuclear arms development program and other issues. 
  It will be the first summit on the Korean peninsula, divided 
since 1948. 

</TEXT>

