<H3> <TI>   Hitachi To Move TV Plant From Malaysia to Mexico </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hitachi To Move TV Plant From Malaysia to Mexico </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1906082194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0128 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1906082194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 19 KYODO -- Hitachi Ltd., Japan's 
largest comprehensive electric machinery manufacturer, will 
shift production of television chassis at its plant in Malaysia 
to Mexico, a leading business daily said Sunday. 
  According to the NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN, the company's 
production shift will be made to cope with the North American 
Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA), which took effect in January. 
  The company will begin manufacturing tv chassis this summer 
at a plant in Tiajuana on the U.S.-Mexico border. Hitachi will 
aim to produce chassis for 500,000 TV sets annually during a 
five-year period, the paper said. 
  Hitachi's move is expected to facilitate other Japanese 
electric makers' plans to shift their productions to Mexico to 
avoid disadvantageous tariffs on goods manufactured outside 
North America, it added. 

</TEXT>

