  [Text] Tokyo, June 17 KYODO -- Japan will extend emergency 
humanitarian aid totaling 78,000 dollars worth of medical goods 
and equipment to three former Soviet Union republics in central 
Asia, the Foreign Ministry said Friday [17 June]. 
  The aid will be extended to Turkmenistan, Kyrgyzstan and 
Tajikistan, the ministry said. The three nations will each 
receive 2 tons of medical goods and equipment, enough to cover 
the medical needs of 20,000 people for three months, it said. 

