<F P=100> Indonesia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Hails Resolution on Arms Supply </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Hails Resolution on Arms Supply </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1806143694 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1806143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Indonesia has expressed its full support to the 
United Nations Security Council resolution No. 924 calling for 
an immediate end to the supply of arms and other forms of 
assistance to any group that is involved in the armed conflict 
in Yemen. This is aimed at preventing the spread of the civil 
war in that country. 
  According to a press statement released by the Foreign 
Affairs Department in Jakarta today, Indonesia is reiterating 
its call to those involved in the conflict to immediately stop 
the exchange of fire and make efforts to seek a peaceful 
solution to the civil war in that country. 
  The statement says Indonesia is concerned at the continuing 
armed conflict there, which has resulted in an increasing number 
of casualties and damage to property. 

</TEXT>

