  [Text] A high-ranking Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC] 
delegation led by Prince Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh and Samdech 
Hun Sen, the first and second prime ministers of the RGC, left 
Phnom Penh at 0730 this morning on a three-day official visit to 
Indonesia -- 20-22 June -- at the invitation of His Excellency 
[H.E.] Indonesian President Suharto. Accompanying the 
delegation was Prince Kromkhun Norodom Sirivut, deputy prime 
minister and minister of foreign affairs and international 
cooperation, and a number of other officials. 
  Seeing the high-ranking delegation off at Pochentong Airport 
were H.E. Sar Kheng, deputy prime minister and co-minister of 
the interior, and their excellencies the state ministers, 
officials, and diplomatic corps accredited to the Kingdom of 
Cambodia. 
  The visit is aimed at strengthening and expanding 
cooperation 
between the two countries of Cambodia and Indonesia. During the 
visit, it is expected that the two prime ministers will sign 
three documents, including a joint communique. 

</TEXT>

