<H3> <TI>   `No Desire' To Become Premier </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `No Desire' To Become Premier </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1906125394 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1200 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1906125394 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 1200 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  ["Message from His Majesty the King to Samdech Hun Sen, 
second prime minister of the Royal Government of Cambodia"; 
dated 18 June -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] To His Excellency [H.E.] Samdech Hun Sen, second 
prime minister of the Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC]. 
  Samdech: I would like to reassure you that I have no desire 
to become the prime minister of Cambodia. I am an old man and 
suffering serious illnesses. 
  This year I must stay in the Beijing Hospital for two or 
three months. After leaving the hospital, I must continue 
receiving medical treatment until January 1995. I must get this 
medical treatment in Beijing and Pyongyang. In 1995 I hope to 
be able to visit my most beloved children, grand children, and 
great-grandchildren, that is, my esteemed Cambodian people. 
Moreover, in 1995 and the years to come, I have no desire to 
control the state power. 
  Please, H.E. Samdech Hun Sen, accept my highest regards. 
  [Dated] Beijing, 18 June 1994 
  [Signed] Norodom Sihanouk 

</TEXT>

