<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage Continues on Roundtable Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage Continues on Roundtable Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Phnom Penh Office Closed </H4>

<F P=102> OW2006100094 Tokyo KYODO in English 0944 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2006100094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom penh, June 20 KYODO -- The Khmer Rouge rebel 
group formally closed its office in Phnom Penh on Monday [20 
June] and its seven remaining officials in the capital flew to 
Thailand. 
  The government notified the Khmer Rouge on Friday that it 
could not guarantee the safety of its representatives following 
the breakdown last week of roundtable peace talks between the 
coalition government and the guerrilla faction. 
  Before their departure, the seven Khmer Rouge officials 
issued a statement saying that they have no intention of bidding 
farewell to the citizens of Phnom Penh and voicing hope to 
return again sometime in the future. 
  Other senior Khmer Rouge officials in Phnom Penh had 
departed 
Saturday. 

</TEXT>

