  [Excerpt] East Timor will have an observer at the Lusophone 
countries summit. The proposal was made and the response was 
also positive. What remains to be seen is who will represent 
East Timor: 
  [Begin Ramos Horta, Revolutionary Front for an Independent 
East Timor, spokesman abroad telephone recording] What we want 
is to obtain a status of a permanent observer country. East 
Timor is not yet an independent country but we have the right to 
have an observer representation at the summit. If East Timor 
were an independent country, we would then be a country with 
full rights. We have been told by the PALOPs [Portuguese 
Speaking African Countries] and Brazil that the East Timor issue 
will be on the agenda, that there will be an East Timorese 
resistance representation, and what remains to be defined is who 
will represent East Timor, who will represent the East Timorese 
resistance. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

