<H3> <TI>   U.S. Insurance Firm Approved To Operate in Japan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Insurance Firm Approved To Operate in Japan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2006062394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0528 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2006062394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 20 KYODO -- The Ministry of Finance on 
Monday [20 June] gave approval to Unum Life Insurance Co., a 
major U.S. accident insurance company, to sell workers' accident 
compensation insurance in Japan, ministry officials said. 
  The company, based in Portland, Maine, will set up its 
Japanese unit in Tokyo at a capital of 3 billion yen and start 
its operations in October, the officials said. 
  Unum will sell a new type of insurance that assures 
long-term 
compensation of income for the insured, who are unable to keep 
working because of injuries and diseases, the officials said. 

</TEXT>

