<H3> <TI>   Air Defense Exercise Scheduled 23 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Air Defense Exercise Scheduled 23 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2106041094 Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA in English 0304 GMT 21 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2106041094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur BERNAMA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kuala Lumpur, June 21 (OANA-BERNAMA) -- The Air 
Forces of Malaysia and Singapore will hold a one-day air defence 
exercise on Thursday under the Five Power Defence Arrangement 
(FPDA), the Ministry of Defence said here Tuesday. 
  Codenamed Minor Adex 94, the exercise was aimed at examining 
the air defence forces of member countries against a simulated 
external air threat. 
  It would be co-ordinated by the Integrated Air Defence 
System 
headquarters at the Royal Malaysian Air Force (RMAF) base in 
Butterworth, northern Pulau Penang state. 
  Malaysian aircraft involved in the exercise include the 
Northrop F-5E jetfighter and PC-130 patrol aircraft while the 
Republic of Singapore Air Force (RSAF) will deploy its F-16 
Falcon, A-4S Superskyhawk fighter bombers and C-130 Hercules 
transport aircraft. 
  The RSAF will also deploy the improved Hawk missile system 
for air defence and a 35-mm anti-aircraft gun battery for the 
exercise to be conducted in Malaysian and Singapore air space. 

</TEXT>

