<H3> <TI>   Minister: No Work Permits for British Firms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister: No Work Permits for British Firms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1806113094 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 
GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1806113094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The federal government will not issue work permits 
to British companies involving themselves in the Kelantan 
government under the water supply privatization project in the 
east coast state. Rural Development Minister Annuar Musa said 
this was because the ban on British companies is still in force 
and the state government's need to have dealings with British 
companies contradicts the federal government's policy. 
  Speaking to newsmen in Kota Baru, he said the state 
government's decision to have joint ventures with British 
companies did not violate any law since such dealings were 
within its jurisdiction. But the issuance of work permits came 
under the purview of the federal government. 
  Encik [Mr.] Annuar said that Kelantan's (?new) deal on the 
privatization project fatefully has raised doubts. 

</TEXT>

