<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ranariddh, Hun Sen To Visit Indonesia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ranariddh, Hun Sen To Visit Indonesia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1806101394 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0415 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1806101394 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [All quotation marks as received] </F>
  [Text] Phnom Penh 18 Jun (AKP) -- At the invitation of 
Sukarno, president of the Republic of Indonesia, a high-ranking 
delegation of the Royal Government of Cambodia [RGC], will leave 
for Indonesia for an official three-day visit" according to a 
communique made public in Phnom Penh on 17 June. 
  "The high-ranking Cambodian delegation will be led by Prince 
Krompreah Norodom Ranariddh and Samdech Hun Sen, RGC first and 
second prime ministers. 
  "This visit will take place from 20 to 22 June," specifies 
the communique. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

