  [Text] The following is the content of the letter from the 
two-headed government's interior ministers to the Party of 
Democratic Kampuchea's [PDK] representatives in Phnom Penh: 
  The Ministry of the Interior requests that all PDK 
representatives and their staff leave Phnom Penh immediately -- 
before 19 June 1994. The Ministry of the Interior will provide 
safe escort for your group's trip from its office to Pochentong 
Airport. You must inform the Ministry of the Interior at least 
one day before your departure, however. The Ministry of the 
Interior will not be responsible for your security beyond the 
deadline stated above. 
  [Dated] 17 June 1994 
  [Signed] Sar Kheng and Yu Hokkri 

