<H3> <TI>   Battle in Kompong Speu Province 14 Jun Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Battle in Kompong Speu Province 14 Jun Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1806104094 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1806104094 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 14 June, the people and the National Army of 
Democratic Kampuchea [NADK] cooperated in attacking and 
completely dispersing the military and civilian state authority 
of the puppets of communist Vietnam in Trapeang Kraloeng, Phnum 
Sruch district seat, Kompong Speu Province. 
  After a battle lasting an hour, we fully controlled this 
district township. Fifteen of the invading troops of the 
puppets of communist Vietnam were killed and eight others 
wounded. Ten army shelters and three district office buildings 
were destroyed. We seized eight AK rifles, three AR-15's, and 
three (BH) mines. 
  At the same time, 20 soldiers of the puppets of communist 
Vietnam and 11 officials serving the communist Vietnam's puppets 
surrendered and joined the people and the NADK. They said that 
they will stop serving the communist Vietnamese, who are 
continuing to attack and kill the nation. These compatriots 
asked to join forces with the people and the NADK to fight the 
military and civilian state authorities of the puppets of 
communist Vietnam to quickly destroy them so that there will be 
peace, without anyone forcing the compatriots to fight. 
  However, the people and the NADK suggested that these 
compatriots return home and join forces with the people in their 
localities to fight the warmongers in their dens. This way 
there will be no one to force the compatriots to fight and die, 
leaving their families behind, and there will be no one to force 
compatriots to round up the people's relatives to serve as 
soldiers --- an act which makes the people angry and causes them 
to loath and hurl insults at these compatriots. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

