<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Memorandum on Archiving Assistance Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Memorandum on Archiving Assistance Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2006132094 Vientiane KPL in English 0923 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2006132094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, June 17 [date as received] (KPL) -- The 
Vietnamese Archive Department has agreed to help the Lao Archive 
Department in training archivists and data collection. 
  A memorandum of understanding on the assistance was signed 
here between the deputy director of the Lao department, 
Thongsivang, and his Vietnamese counterpart, who is on the 
current visit to Laos. 
  According to the memorandum, the Vietnamese side will help 
train Lao technicians in this field and collect information on 
Lao archives. Both sides also will exchange technicians 
concerned with archives. 

</TEXT>

